name: gwcelery
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "gwcelery" %}
{% set version = "1.0.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d154c48d0cd6369b38545b95ccb6d427ff35a52845a2f9c5a683610af201a6ce
  patches:
    # update requirements for conda
    - requirements.patch

build:
  entry_points:
    - gwcelery = gwcelery:main
    - gwcelery-condor-submit-helper = gwcelery.tools.condor_submit_helper:main
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.8
    - poetry-core >=1.0.0
    - poetry-dynamic-versioning
  run:
    - astropy >=4.3.1
    - bilby_pipe >=0.3.8
    - celery >=5.1
    - click 7
    - comet
    - corner
    - dnspython
    - flask
    - flask-caching
    - gracedb-sdk >=0.1.5
    - gwdatafind
    - gwpy >=2.0.1
    - healpy
    - imapclient
    - jinja2 >=2.11.2
    - ligo-followup-advocate >=1.1.6
    - ligo-gracedb >=2.7.5
    - ligo-raven >=2.0
    - ligo-segments
    - ligo.em-bright >=1.0
    - ligo.skymap >=0.4.0
    - lscsoft-glue
    - lxml
    - numpy
    - p_astro >=1.0
    - pygcn >=1.0.1
    - python >=3.8
    - python-lal >=7.1.2
    - python-ligo-lw >=1.7.0,<1.8.0a0
    - redis-py
    - safe-netrc
    - sentry-sdk
    - service_identity
    - sleek-lvalert <2.0.0
    - voeventlib >=1.2
    - werkzeug >=0.15.0
    - zstandard
    # extras for sentry-sdk[flask]
    - blinker >=1.1
    # extras for sentry-sdk[tornado]
    - tornado >=5

test:
  requires:
    # for scikit-learn
    - openblas
    # for mpi
    - openssh
    # for pip check
    - pip
    # for gwcelery's test suite
    - pytest >=3.0
    - pytest-celery
    - pytest-flask
    - pytest-socket
    # to help 'pip check'
    - arviz >=0.12.1
  commands:
    # check requirements
    - python -m pip check
    # run test suite
    - python -m pytest --pyargs gwcelery
    # check entry points
    - gwcelery report

about:
  home: https://git.ligo.org/emfollow/gwcelery
  dev_url: https://git.ligo.org/emfollow/gwcelery
  doc_url: https://gwcelery.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: LICENSE.rst
  summary: Hipster pipeline for annotating LIGO events
  description: |
    GWCelery is a simple and reliable package for annotating and orchestrating
    LIGO/Virgo alerts, built from widely used open source components.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - duncanmmacleod
